==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enfleurage
<hw>En`fleu`rage"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>en-</ets> (L. in) + <ets>fleur</ets> flower.]</ety> <def>A process
of extracting perfumes by exposing absorbents, as fixed oils or fats, to
the exhalations of the flowers. It is used for plants whose volatile
oils are too delicate to be separated by distillation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enflower</ent>⟦br⟧
